sinz 2025-04-25 06:22 p.m.
Based on the egregious conduct of the defendants. Both causes of actionassault and conversionarise from the same incident in which the defendants used firearms to threaten and rob the plaintiff of his property, specifically fish he had caught. This conduct was not only intentional but also malicious. The defendants brandished deadly weapons to place the plaintiff in reasonable fear for his life, satisfying the elements of assault. While no compensatory damages are sought for this count, punitive damages in the amount of $50,000 per defendant are appropriate to punish and deter this kind of violent and threatening behavior.

In relation to the second cause of action, conversion under 5 M.S.C. 1 3103.3, the defendants again acted willfully and with malice. They used the threat of lethal force to take property that did not belong to them, depriving the plaintiff of its use and value. The compensatory damages of 1,450 Clark cash reflect the market value of the stolen property based on @mrntee testimony, but do not fully account for the aggravated manner in which the theft was carried out. For this reason, an additional $60,000 in punitive damages per defendant is justified. We believe this is necessary to fulfill the goals of punishment and deterrence.

Defendants can easily get this money with a little bit of logging and we are okay with taking cash by payments if necessary
